  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `v1.10.8`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nclient `FilterLogs` to resolve with an error\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nRPC provider: Alchemy\r\nRarely, when `eth_getLogs` resolves with 500 from Alchemy provider, the goethereum `filterLogs` does not resolve with neither error, nor any response. It seems that the query gets stuck and does not continue further with the business logic. Below I am providing pseudocode of an infinite `for loop` that queries for events every 15 seconds. What is experienced is that `evmClient.FilterLogs(context.Background(), *query)` does not resolve and everything gets stuck.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\npseudocode:\r\n```go\r\nfunc main() {\r\n\r\n\tsleepDuration := 15 * time.Second\r\n\r\n\trpcUrl := \"\" // Alchemy RPC url\r\n\r\n\tevmClient, err := ethclient.Dial(rpcUrl)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tlog.Fatalf(\"Failed to initialize Client. Error [%s]\", err)\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tcontractAddress := []common.Address{}\r\n\taddresses := []common.Address{\r\n\t\t// Contract addresses\r\n\t}\r\n\ttopics := [][]common.Hash{\r\n\t\t{\r\n\t\t\t// Topic IDs\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tfor {\r\n\t\t// Gets start block from DB\r\n\t\tfromBlock, err := db.GetLastBlock(contractAddress)\r\n\t\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\t\tlog.Errorf(\"Failed to retrieve fromBlock. Error: [%s]\", err)\r\n                        time.sleep(sleepDuration)\r\n\t\t\tcontinue\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n\t\ttoBlock, err := evmClient.BlockNumber(context.Background())\r\n\t\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\t\tlog.Errorf(\"Failed to retrieve latest block number. Error [%s]\", err)\r\n\t\t\ttime.Sleep(sleepDuration)\r\n\t\t\tcontinue\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n\t\tquery := &ethereum.FilterQuery{\r\n\t\t\tFromBlock: new(big.Int).SetInt64(fromBlock),\r\n\t\t\tToBlock:   new(big.Int).SetInt64(int64(toBlock)),\r\n\t\t\tAddresses: addresses,\r\n\t\t\tTopics:    topics,\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n\t\tlogs, err := evmClient.FilterLogs(context.Background(), *query)\r\n\t\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\t\tlog.Errorf(\"Failed to to filter logs. Error: [%s]\", err)\r\n\t\t\ttime.Sleep(sleepDuration)\r\n\t\t\tcontinue\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\t//processLogs(logs) // Process logs\r\n                err := db.UpdateLastBlock(toBlock + 1)\r\n                if err != nil {\r\n\t\t\tlog.Errorf(\"Failed to update last block. Error: [%s]\", err)\r\n                        time.sleep(sleepDuration)\r\n\t\t\tcontinue\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n\t\ttime.Sleep(sleepDuration)\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n\r\n```",
